preibisch_imagelib2.algorithm.componenttree.mser

Class Mser<T extends Type<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • preibisch_imagelib2.algorithm.componenttree.mser.Mser<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - value type of the input image.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Localizable>, Component<T,Mser<T>>

    public final class Mser<T extends Type<T>>
extends Object
implements Component<T,Mser<T>>
    A maximally stable extremal region (MSER) of the image thresholded at value(). The set of pixels can be accessed by iterating ( iterator()) the component. This is a node in a MserTree. The child and parent nodes can be accessed by getChildren() and getParent().
    Author:
    Tobias Pietzsch
